	<div class="content clearfix">
		
		<ul class="faq-list">
			<li> 
			<h5>
				Do all iPads use the same type of SIM card?
			</h5>
			<p>
				No. iPad mini uses a nano-SIM card. All other iPad models use a micro-SIM card. Micro-SIM cards cannot be used in devices that use nano-SIM cards.
			</p>
<p><a href="http://www.apple.com/ipad/LTE" class="more" onclick="s_objectID='66e33fb37a91c6e57bd270c304edcbd8';"  data-evar1="AOS: home/shop_ipad/family/ipad_mini/select | learn-more-1 | Astro Link | 0 | http://www.apple.com/ipad/LTE" data-evar30="home/shop_ipad/family/ipad_mini/select/learn-more-1">Click here for information on iPad support for LTE networks by carrier and country</a></p>

			</li>
			
		</ul>
		<ul class="faq-list last">
			<li> 
			<h5>
				Do accessories for iPad 2 and the third-generation iPad work with iPad with Retina display or iPad mini? 

			</h5>
			<p>
				iPad with Retina display and iPad mini use the Lightning connector, which is different from the 30-pin connector on iPad 2 and the third-generation iPad. However, you can purchase a Lightning to 30-pin Adapter to use with existing 30-pin accessories (except those that require video output). For more information about compatibility, visit the <a href=" http://store.apple.com/us/browse/home/shop_ipad/ipad_accessories">iPad accessory</a> pages on the Apple Online Store.  
			</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<div class="nested-footer trigger">
			<a href="#" class="scroll-to"><span class="close">Close</span></a>
		</div>


	</div>
</div>

